snippet: Former Haitian President Rene Preval, 74, the first leader in Haiti's history to win a democratic election, serve a full term and peacefully hand power to a successor, died on Friday after falling unconscious at his home....

headline.main: New Interior Chief Vows Review of Obama-Era Rules,' Bold' Restructuring
headline.print_headline: New Interior Chief Vows Review of Obama-Era Rules,' Bold' Restructuring

lead_paragraph: Former Haitian President Rene Preval, 74, the first leader in Haiti's history to win a democratic election, serve a full term and peacefully hand power to a successor, died on Friday after falling unconscious at his home.
